Files to edit:
- `platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/PluginIcon.tsx` — Remove the entire `StatusIndicator` component (lines 77-137). Remove `hasUpdate` from `PluginIconProps` interface and from the component's destructured props. The icon container div (line 179 for SVG mode, line 198 for letter avatar mode) currently has `rounded border-2 border-border`. Change this to be dynamic based on `tabState` and `active`:
  - Ready + idle: `border-2 border-border`
  - Ready + active: `border-2 border-primary animate-activity-border-flash`
  - Ready + fading out: `border-2 border-primary animate-activity-border-fade-out`
  - Not ready (unavailable/closed): `border-2 border-border/30`
  The fade-out logic (useRef + useEffect for active→inactive transition) currently lives inside StatusIndicator — move it to the PluginIcon component itself since the border container needs it.

- `platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/styles.css` — Add two new animation classes:
  ```css
  @keyframes activity-border-flash {
    0%, 100% { border-color: var(--primary); }
    50% { border-color: var(--border); }
  }
  .animate-activity-border-flash {
    animation: activity-border-flash 0.4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  @keyframes activity-border-fade-out {
    from { border-color: var(--primary); }
    to { border-color: var(--border); }
  }
  .animate-activity-border-fade-out {
    animation: activity-border-fade-out 0.5s ease-out forwards;
  }
  ```
  The not-ready state uses `border-border/30` (Tailwind opacity modifier) — this does NOT need a new animation, just a conditional class.
  Keep the existing `activity-flash` and `activity-fade-out` keyframes — they will still be used by ToolIcon (US-002).

- `platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/PluginIcon.stories.tsx` — Remove the `ReadyWithUpdate` story. Update the `Palette` story to no longer pass `hasUpdate`. Add an `ActiveBorderFlash` story showing active=true with tabState='ready'. The existing `Active` and `ActiveFadeOut` stories should still work.

- `platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/PluginIcon.test.ts` — No changes needed, the test file only tests `hashString`, `getAvatarVar`, `getAvatarLetter`, and `tryGetSanitizedSvg` which are unaffected.

- `platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/PluginCard.tsx` — Remove `hasUpdate={!!plugin.update}` from the PluginIcon usage (line 149). Keep passing `active={hasActiveTool}`.

- `platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/BrowserToolsCard.tsx` — No changes needed (BrowserToolsCard never passes hasUpdate).

IMPORTANT: The border animation for the not-ready state with faded border uses `border-border/30`. When the active animation plays on a ready plugin, the border pulses between `var(--primary)` (yellow) and `var(--border)` (black/gray). Make sure the `animate-activity-border-fade-out` animation's `to` keyframe uses `var(--border)` so it settles back to the correct resting state.
